A vintage 1960s-style illustration of a frazzled office worker drowning in an ocean made entirely of white paper envelopes, their arms reaching upward desperately. The envelopes form towering waves around them, some cascading down like waterfalls. The color palette uses muted teals, warm oranges, and cream tones typical of mid-century advertising. The worker wears a crisp white shirt with rolled sleeves, their expression overwhelmed but slightly comical. In the background, a massive analog clock looms like a sun setting on the horizon, its hands spinning rapidly in a blur. The entire scene has a slightly grainy texture and halftone dots reminiscent of vintage magazine prints.
